              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASPEC",
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Cross sections were deduced from the",
                "count of alpha-decay chains. Dubnium compound",
                "nucleus evaporation residues are formed with the",
                "momentum of the projectile and recoil from the",
                "target. After separation in the BGS, the dubnium",
                "recoils passed through a multiwire proportional",
                "counter (MWPC) and were implanted into a focal plane",
                "detector (FPD). The FPD was composed of an",
                "implantation detector and an upstream detector. The",
                "implantation detector consisted of three silicon",
                "cards, each containing 16 vertical strips that",
                "allowed for determination of the horizontal position.",
                "Energy was calibrated using a four-point alpha source",
                "containing 148Gd, 239Pu, 241Am, and 244Cm. Events",
                "identified as alpha particles were required to be",
                "anticoincident with the MWPC and punch-through",
                "detectors, in the same strip as and within a vertical",
                "position of +-3 sigma of the evaporation residue."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
